.START 

This Los Angeles company and its Union Federal Savings Bank subsidiary said more than 99% of their 7 1/4% convertible subordinated debentures due 2011 were tendered for conversion into UnionFed common stock.
The conversion increased total equity capital by about $38.5 million to a total of $156.8 million.
Union Federal, a federally insured savings bank, has $2.4 billion in assets. 

